  - "② Pay attention to bracket types: $-2$ and $5$ belong to the set (filled dots on the axis), so the brackets next to these numbers should be square brackets $[\\,$ and $\\,]$."
  - "③ The matching answer is exactly $(-\\infty,\\,-2] \\cup [5,\\,+\\infty)$ — two unbounded closed intervals joined by a set union."
tests:
  abs_value: 1.0
