  - "① Perpendicularity of two lines in slope-intercept form depends only on their slopes — the y-intercept doesn't matter."
  - "② Use the perpendicularity condition: $a_1 \\cdot a_2 = -1$, where $a_1, a_2$ are the slopes of the two lines."
  - "③ Here $a_1 = m+1$ and $a_2 = -2$, so $(m+1)\\cdot(-2) = -1$, hence $m + 1 = \\frac{1}{2}$ and $m = -\\frac{1}{2}$."
