  - "② The critical point $a=24$ does NOT belong to the domain $(0,\\,8\\sqrt{3}]$, since $8\\sqrt{3}\\approx 13.86<24$. Throughout the domain $P'(a)<0$ (the function is decreasing), so the minimum is at the RIGHT endpoint of the interval."
  - "③ Minimum at $a=8\\sqrt{3}$: $P(8\\sqrt{3})=\\dfrac{(8\\sqrt{3})^2\\sqrt{3}}{2}+\\dfrac{13824\\sqrt{3}}{8\\sqrt{3}}=\\dfrac{192\\sqrt{3}}{2}+1728=96\\sqrt{3}+1728$."
tests:
  optimization_lp: 1.0
  deriv_apps: 0.7
