  - "① We have $V(h)=\\dfrac{\\pi}{3}\\cdot\\dfrac{25h^3}{h^2-25}$ for $h>5$. Compute the derivative and set it equal to zero, applying the quotient rule."
  - "② $V'(h)=\\dfrac{25\\pi}{3}\\cdot\\dfrac{3h^2(h^2-25)-h^3\\cdot 2h}{(h^2-25)^2}=\\dfrac{25\\pi}{3}\\cdot\\dfrac{h^2(h^2-75)}{(h^2-25)^2}$. Zero at $h^2=75$, so $h=5\\sqrt{3}$."
  - "③ Substitute: $V(5\\sqrt{3})=\\dfrac{\\pi}{3}\\cdot\\dfrac{25\\cdot 125\\cdot 3\\sqrt{3}}{75-25}=\\dfrac{\\pi}{3}\\cdot\\dfrac{9375\\sqrt{3}}{50}=\\dfrac{125\\pi\\sqrt{3}}{2}$."
